==Latin==
===Etymology===
From Indo-European ''*mr̥-, *mr̥-to-'' ‘death’.  Cognate with [[Ancient Greek]] [[βροτός]] ‘mortal’ (from an earlier form ''*μροτός''), Germanic ''*murþaz'' (Old English [[morþ]], English [[murder]]), Celtic ''*marwo-'' (Old Irish [[marb]], Welsh [[marw]] ‘died’), Lithuanian [[mirtìs]] ‘death’.

===Noun===
'''mors, mortis'''  ''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin third declension|3rd declension]]''

# [[death]]
# [[corpse]]
# [[annihilation]]

